President Donald J. Trump has submitted a letter to the Chairman (or Chairwoman) in accordance with section 303(a)(6)(A) of the Defense Production Act of 1950. The letter addresses a shortfall in the defense industrial base concerning the production capability for ultra-high and high temperature composites (U/HTC) for hypersonic, strategic missile, and space launch systems. The Department of Defense will take actions to develop and acquire equipment and materials necessary for creating, maintaining, protecting, and expanding the production capability for these composites. President Trump asserts that these initiatives are crucial for national defense.